  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <div id="score-container">Score: <span id="score">0</span></div>
  <style>
body, html {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

#game-container {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

#dog {
  position: absolute;
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 50%;
  width: 200px;
  height: auto;
}

#ball {
  position: absolute;
  width: 50px;
  height: auto;
}

#score-container {
  position: absolute;
  top: 10px;
  right: 10px;
  font-size: 20px;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

  </style>

<body>
  <div id="game-container">
    <img id="dog" src="data:image/gif;base64," alt="dog">
    <img id="ball" src="data:image/png;base64," alt="ball">
  </div>
  <script>
 const dog = document.getElementById('dog');
const ball = document.getElementById('ball');
let dogPosition = window.innerWidth / 2;
let ballPositionX = Math.random() * window.innerWidth;
let ballPositionY = 0;
let gameOver = false;
let score = 0;

document.addEventListener('click', (event) => {
  const clickPosition = event.clientX;

  if (clickPosition < dogPosition + dog.clientWidth / 2) {
    dogPosition -= 30;
  } else {
    dogPosition += 30;
  }

  dogPosition = Math.min(Math.max(dogPosition, 0), window.innerWidth - dog.clientWidth);
  dog.style.left = `${dogPosition}px`;
});

document.addEventListener('mousedown', (event) => {
  event.preventDefault();
});

function gameLoop() {
  if (gameOver) return;

  ballPositionY += 3;
  ball.style.top = `${ballPositionY}px`;

  if (ballPositionY > window.innerHeight) {
    ballPositionX = Math.random() * window.innerWidth;
    ball.style.left = `${ballPositionX}px`;
    ballPositionY = 0;
  }

  const dogRect = dog.getBoundingClientRect();
  const ballRect = ball.getBoundingClientRect();
  const scoreDisplay = document.getElementById('score');

  if (dogRect.left < ballRect.right &&
    dogRect.right > ballRect.left &&
    dogRect.top < ballRect.bottom &&
    dogRect.bottom > ballRect.top) {
  score += 1;
  scoreDisplay.textContent = score; // 
  ballPositionX = Math.random() * window.innerWidth;
  ball.style.left = `${ballPositionX}px`;
  ballPositionY = 0;
}

  requestAnimationFrame(gameLoop);
}

gameLoop();

  </script>
</body>
</html>
